Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.94,0:00:08.11,Default,MASHA,0,0,0,,We're back.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.11,0:00:11.07,Default,TOYA,0,0,0,,Hey, welcome back. Thanks...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.07,0:00:13.82,Default,TOYA,0,0,0,,What's that thing you're holding?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.34,0:00:15.76,Default,MASHA,0,0,0,,Isn't it cute?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.76,0:00:18.04,Default,TOYA,0,0,0,,It certainly is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.04,0:00:20.70,Default,TOYA,0,0,0,,but please don't tell me \Nyou're going to keep it here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.05,0:00:22.96,Default,MASHA,0,0,0,,May I?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.21,0:00:25.85,Default,TOYA,0,0,0,,I beg you, please reconsider.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.37,0:00:30.10,Default,MASACHIKA,0,0,0,,Here are the supplies we got.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.10,0:00:31.17,Default,TOYA,0,0,0,,Let me see.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.61,0:00:34.05,Default,TOYA,0,0,0,,Okay, perfectly ordinary supplies.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.42,0:00:36.28,Default,TOYA,0,0,0,,You're a lifesaver, Kuze.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.28,0:00:39.38,Default,TOYA,0,0,0,,Who knows what the elder Kujo would've\N done if left to her own devices?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.11,0:00:44.07,Default,MASACHIKA,0,0,0,,The student council office \Nwould've become a theme park.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.90,0:00:50.45,Default,TOYA,0,0,0,,Well, Kuze? Changed your mind \Non joining the student council yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.45,0:00:53.86,Default,MASACHIKA,0,0,0,,No, though I wouldn't mind \Nhelping out occasionally.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.86,0:00:58.32,Default,MASHA,0,0,0,,Then why not join on paper?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.32,0:01:00.99,Default,TOYA,0,0,0,,I'm glad you agree with \Nbringing him on, Elder Kujo.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.99,0:01:03.62,Default,MASACHIKA,0,0,0,,"On paper"? Come on now...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.62,0:01:06.34,Default,MASACHIKA,0,0,0,,And I understand Yuki wanting me to join,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.34,0:01:09.13,Default,MASACHIKA,0,0,0,,but why are you so set on bringing me on, Prez?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.43,0:01:13.79,Default,TOYA,0,0,0,,Why are {\i1}you{\i0} so set on not joining?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.79,0:01:17.01,Default,TOYA,0,0,0,,Something tells me there's more \Nto it than all the work involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.61,0:01:21.76,Default,MASACHIKA,0,0,0,,I'm not worthy of being \Na student council officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.25,0:01:25.85,Default,TOYA,0,0,0,,"Not worthy"? I can't say I agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.85,0:01:32.11,Default,TOYA,0,0,0,,After all, you were a fine vice president \Nfor the middle school's student council.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.11,0:01:35.19,Default,MASACHIKA,0,0,0,,That experience is what proved it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.19,0:01:39.78,Default,MASACHIKA,0,0,0,,I didn't have any suitable goals that I could\Nuse that position of power to achieve.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.44,0:01:44.60,Default,TOYA,0,0,0,,And what's wrong with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.60,0:01:45.29,Default,MASACHIKA,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.57,0:01:51.00,Default,TOYA,0,0,0,,I became student council president \Nto win the heart of the girl I love.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.00,0:01:54.55,Default,TOYA,0,0,0,,A reason far more improper \Nthan any you may have.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.03,0:01:59.96,Default,MASACHIKA,0,0,0,,Wait, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.97,0:02:02.54,Default,TOYA,0,0,0,,Take a look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.62,0:02:05.47,Default,MASACHIKA,0,0,0,,Is that your younger brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.02,0:02:08.10,Default,TOYA,0,0,0,,That was me back in ninth grade.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.87,0:02:10.48,Default,MASACHIKA,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.34,0:02:12.07,Default,MASACHIKA,0,0,0,,What?
